4 different games are played: mah-jongg, snooker, go, whist
The people use 4 different means of transport: ship, airplane, jet-ski, train
4 different pets are kept: frog, mouse, snake, chinchilla
1. the owner of the mouse is on the right of the person playing go##1
2. the person driving the train is the person drinking hot-chocolate##1
3. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left or right of the person drinking sprite##3
4. the owner of the chinchilla is somewhere to the right of the person playing snooker##5
5. the person drinking hot-chocolate is on the left of the owner of the chinchilla##1
6. the person drinking fanta is on the right of the person driving the jet-ski##1
7. the person driving the airplane is somewhere to the left of the person drinking fanta##5
8. the person driving the airplane is between the owner of the mouse and the owner of the snake##2
9. the person playing mah-jongg is somewhere to the left of the person playing whist##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |       1       |      2       |     3      |     4      |
| Beverage      | hot-chocolate | sprite       | iced-tea   | fanta      |
| Game         | snooker         | go | mah-jongg | whist    |
| Transport   | train        | airplane          | jet-ski        | ship    |
| Pet         | snake      | chinchilla       | mouse | frog |

